<HL>
   Business Brief -- Porta Systems Corp.:
   Concern to Pay $6.7 Million
   To Acquire Electronics Firm
</HL>
<DATE>
08/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C21
</SO>
<CO>
   PSI NOHL
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Porta Systems Corp. agreed to pay $2.50 a share, or about
$6.7 million, for North Hills Electronics Inc., a Glen Cove,
N.Y., manufacturer of connection products used in
data-communications networks.
   The acquisition would broaden Syosset, N.Y.-based Porta
Systems' lines of connection, protection and testing devices
for telecommunications use, said Vincent Santulli, Porta
Systems' chairman and chief executive officer.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   For the first quarter ended April 30, North Hills earnings
more than tripled to $77,886, or three cents a share, as
sales climbed 22% to $3.5 million.
   The acquisition is subject to execution of a definitive
agreement, approval by North Hills stockholders, and other
conditions.
</TEXT>
